place.name: EYEWORTH
place.gazetteerText: EYWORTH, a parish in Biggleswade district, Beds; near the boundary with Cambridge and Herts, 4 miles E by N of Biggleswade town and r. station. Post town, Biggleswade. Acres, 1, 229. Real property, £1, 385. Pop., 149. Houses, 28. The property is all in one estate. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Ely. Value, £96. Patron, Lord Ongley. The church is good; and there are charities £17. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
